properties.headline: Flood Warning issued January 7 at 8:53AM AKST until January 10 at 3:00PM AKST by NWS Anchorage AK
properties.description:
The National Weather Service in Anchorage has extended the

* Flood Warning for...
An Ice Jam in...
the Kenai River at Big Eddy.

* Until 300 PM AKST Friday.

* On Monday, the Kenai Peninsula Borough reported an ice jam near
Big Eddy State Recreation Site which is causing flooding in the
Riverside Drive Subdivision.  As of Monday morning there was water
in the Riverside Drive subdivision and water was flowing over
Riverside Lane and Eddy Lane.  Vehicle access is not currently
possible past Amiyung Drive on Eddy Lane. Please do not drive
vehicles in this area for both safety and to prevent road damage.

* With the ongoing cold temperatures, the ice jam could grow
upstream.  Residents between Big Eddy and the Sterling Highway
Bridge should be prepared for rapidly rising water.

* On Monday afternoon, the KPB did a survey of the Ciechanski Road
Subdivision and reports that there is no flooding occurring on the
north side of the river.

* Some locations that will experience flooding include...
locations along the Kenai River between Big Eddy and the Sterling
Highway Bridge.
properties.instruction:
A Flood Warning means that flooding is imminent or occurring. All
interested parties should take necessary precautions immediately.
